President Biden signed three bills into law during a ceremony held at the South Court Auditorium in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building. The first bill aims to cut methane pollution, which is even more dangerous to the climate than previously thought. The second bill protects borrowers from predatory lenders who exploit partnerships with banks to charge exorbitant interest rates. The third bill holds employers accountable for workplace discrimination, ensuring greater accountability, fairness, and justice. The signing ceremony lasted from 5:37 P.M. to 5:45 P.M. EDT.